title: Red Lobster Cheddar Bay Biscuits Copycat Recipe
directions: In a medium mixing bowl, combine Bisquick and cold butter using a fork or pastry cutter. Don't combine too thoroughly - there should be small chunks of butter in your mixture.
Mix in cheese, milk and garlic powder by hand, only until combined.
Drop ¼ cup portions onto an ungreased baking sheet and bake for 15-17 minutes or until golden brown.
After they finish baking, remove the biscuits from the oven.
In a small bowl, combine melted butter, garlic powder, parsley and salt. Brush all of the garlic butter on top of the biscuits, making sure to use all of it.
